div.div:
Every column has one first line, the header.
The first column is a counter starting from 1 and increasing by 1 on each row. The second column (headr TEAM) should shows the name of the clube. The third (header Pts), the number of points gained by the club until the round selected by the user. The fourth (header Pl), the number of games played by the team. The fifth (header W), the number of victories. Sixth (header D), number of draws. Seventh (header L), number of losses. Eigth (header GA), number of goals scored. Ninth (header GA), number of goals against. Tenth, goals difference. Eleventh, percentage of points gained. The last two columns works like a small resume of the last 5 games and the last ten games. The difference between both columns, additionally to the number of rounds to be considered, is the way to show the information to the user. In the case of the last 5 columns, we should show five different symbols, indicating if the result was win, draw loss. In the case of win, we should present to the user a small square or ball, whatever you consider more appropiate, with a letter W and a green background. In the case of a draw, letter D and gray background. Loss, L and red background. The last 10 column, shows the results of the 10 last games in the follow format number of wins-number of draws-number of losses.
The table contains as many lines as clubs registered to the season/league selected by the user.
The initial order should be descending by number of points descending. In the case of two or more clubs with the same number of points, in the future we will implement how to decide the real order, but this will require some changes in the database. For now, we can use the number of wins as the second factor, the third could be the the goals difference, and the last criteria, the number of goals for.Â Â

div.div:
The internal division of columns in a row should be invisibel. The only line who should be visible is the botton line of the row.
The table should show all the games registered on the round being viewed by the user.
Every game generates a row in the table.
The table should be order by the date time of the game.
Every row has the following configuration: A first line containing the stadium where the game were or will be playing followed on the same line by the date and hour of the game. The second line contains club which were or will be plyaing at home, followed by a symbol "X", followed by the club which were or will be playing the game away of home.
